content.text:
Let me analyze the structure and provide assembly instructions:

Analysis of the Main Target Image:
- The structure has multiple layers and consists of different colored blocks (red, yellow, blue, green, and orange)
- It features three arch-like structures made of red blocks
- There are yellow support blocks underneath
- Blue cubic blocks on top
- Green connecting blocks
- Orange triangular/slanted blocks at the end

Block Count and Layer Organization:
- Bottom layer: Yellow rectangular blocks and red arch bases
- Middle layer: Red arch blocks
- Top layer: Green rectangles, blue cubes, and orange triangular pieces

Required Blocks from Dictionary and Assembly Order:

{
Step1: Move block with index 7 (yellow horizontal block - base left)
Step2: Move block with index 7 (yellow horizontal block - base middle)
Step3: Move block with index 7 (yellow horizontal block - base right)
Step4: Move block with index 1 (red arch piece - left)
Step5: Move block with index 1 (red arch piece - middle)
Step6: Move block with index 2 (red arch piece - right)
Step7: Move block with index 8 (yellow horizontal block - top left)
Step8: Move block with index 6 (green horizontal block - right)
Step9: Move block with index 3 (blue cube - back)
Step10: Move block with index 3 (blue cube - front)
Step11: Move block with index 14 (orange triangular piece - right back)
Step12: Move block with index 15 (orange triangular piece - right front)
}

This assembly sequence builds the structure from bottom to top, starting with the base supports, then adding the arches, followed by the connecting pieces, and finally the decorative elements on top.
